    <div xml:id="PN363">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>iruṅkaṭa luṭuttavip peruṅkaṇ mānila</l>
<l>muṭaiyilai naṭuvaṇat tiṭaipiṟark kiṉṟit</l>
<l>tāmē yāṇṭa vēmaṅ kāvala</l>
<l>riṭutirai maṇaliṉum palarē cuṭupiṇak</l>
<l>kāṭupati yākap pōkit tatta</l>
<l>nāṭu piṟarkoḷac ceṉṟumāyn taṉarē</l>
<l>yataṉāl, nīyuṅ kēṇmati yattai vīyā</l>
<l>tuṭampoṭu niṉṟa vuyiru millai</l>
<l>maṭaṅka luṇmai māyamō vaṉṟē</l>
<l>kaḷḷi vēynta muḷḷiyam puṟaṅkāṭṭu</l>
<l>veḷḷil pōkiya viyalu ḷāṅka</l>
<l>ṇuppilāa vavipuḻukkal</l>
<l>kaikkoṇṭu piṟakkunōkkā</l>
<l>tiḻipiṟappiṉō ṉīyappeṟṟu</l>
<l>nilaṅkala ṉāka vilaṅkupali micaiyu</l>
<l>miṉṉā vaikal vārā muṉṉē</l>
<l>ceynnī muṉṉiya viṉaiyē</l>
<l>munnīr varaippaka muḻutuṭaṉ tuṟantē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>On this big earth of vast area that is encircled by the dark sea, (1)</l>
<l>there are protective guardians who rule themselves (3)</l>
<l>without [leaving] for others [as much] space that is in the middle of a babul leaf, (2)</l>
<l>many more that the [grains of] sand by the sea that puts [them down], (4a-c)</l>
<l>Having gone, burning corpses, to the cremation ground as [their] abode, (4d-5c)</l>
<l>as others rule all their lands, they went [and] are gone. (5c-6)</l>
<l>Therefore, you too listen [now]: (7a-c)</l>
<l>there is no lasting life with the body, unperishing. (7d-8)</l>
<l>The existence of Death an illusion? It is not. (9)</l>
<l>In the thorny outer cremation ground covered by spurges, (10)</l>
<l>in that vast inner place overgrown with woodapple (11)</l>
<l>taking in hand boiled rice as an offering </l>
<l>without salt, not looking behind (12f.)</l>
<l>obtaining when a low-born man gives, (14)</l>
<l>on the height of shining offerings with the ground as the vessel, (15)</l>
<l>before unpleasant day comes (16)</l>
<l>[just] do the work you consider, (17)</l>
<l>abandoning altogether the inland bordered by the three-watered sea. (18)</l>
</lg>
